RBNZ sees core inflation peaking at 2 . 7 pct . The Reserve Bank of New Zealand on Friday forecast underlying annual inflation to peak at 2 . 7 percent in the September 1996 quarter . In its six monthly economic projections , the bank forecast the inflation rate to then fall to 2 . 1 percent in the March 1997 year , 0 . 8 percent in the March 1998 year and to 0 . 5 percent the following year . In its June Monetary Policy Statement , the bank forecast inflation would peak at 2 . 6 percent in the September 1996 year before easing back to 1 . 1 percent a year later and to 0 . 3 percent in the September 1998 year . 
